Anadolu Isuzu Otomotiv Sanayi &
Ticaret AS (ASUZU) , the Turkish manufacturer of commercial vehciles for
 Isuzu Motors Ltd. (7202) , surged the most in six months after winning a
25 million-lira ($13.9 million) contract from the city of
Manisa.  The shares jumped 6.6 percent to 10.40 liras at the close
in Istanbul, the biggest gain since Oct. 10.  The company will deliver Isuzu Novo Citi model buses to the
municipality in the second and third quarters of this year,
Anadolu Isuzu said in a statement to the  Istanbul Stock Exchange 
today. It didnâ€™t say how many buses the contract covers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
